  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Considering the Scope**\n\nI\'m starting to visualize a lean, efficient setup. My focus is now on the full-stack landing page and the admin panel, both highly polished. Delving into the main educational event\'s specifics is next.\n\n\n**Defining the Hero Section**\n\nMy latest focus is the hero section design. I\'m leaning towards a modern, minimal aesthetic with a light and airy feel \342\200\223 pure white or a soft grey background. The headline, \"The Main Educational Event of the Year,\" will be prominent. I\'m envisioning a staggered entrance effect and a parallax scroll or elegant interactive layout for visual appeal. A fast registration CTA is, of course, essential. I\'m also planning the hero section content, including key event details.\n\n\n**Developing Core Features**\n\nI\'m now integrating the interactive timeline/schedule, ensuring it\'s fully editable through the admin panel, complete with default lecturers. I\'m also conceptualizing a ticket section with three pricing tiers and customizable benefits, which will also be admin-editable. The partner logos and a subscription form are also coming into view.\n\n\n**Constructing the Admin Panel**\n\nI\'m now deep in the admin panel\'s construction. I\'ve got authorization sorted with basic credential-based login. I\'m focusing on managing speakers, schedule slots, ticket details, and partner information, including UI for image uploads and link edits. I\'m also planning the newsletter export functionality as a CSV download.\n\n\n**Verifying Import Paths**\n\nI\'m now focusing on ensuring correct imports for animations using `motion/react`. I\'ve checked the `package.json` file and verified the `motion` package version. I confirmed that importing from `motion/react` is correct based on the setup. I\'ll test compilation now.\n\n\n**Implementing Server Architecture**\n\nI\'m now implementing the server architecture. I\'ve updated the `package.json` scripts for development, build, and start based on the Express + Vite guideline. This includes using `tsx` and `esbuild` for streamlined development and production builds. I\'m also preparing to create the server-side API routes, and considering proxying requests to keep all API keys hidden from the browser, and the design pattern of storing data in an elegant `/data/` directory.\n\n\n**Structuring the Database**\n\nI\'m now designing the `db.json` structure, aiming for reliability with native `fs/promises` for asynchronous read/write operations. The planned structure includes arrays for speakers, the program, partners, tickets (with dynamic UTM parameters!), subscribers, and essential settings. I\'m focusing on creating realistic default speaker entries \342\200\223 aiming for sixteen representing successful Kazakh and international students admitted to top universities. This will give the application a truly realistic feel.\n\n\n**Translating Core Content**\n\nI\'m now prioritizing the localization, planning for Russian/Kazakh and English content. I\'m focusing on the language switcher for this light, airy aesthetic, and a minimal layout. I\'m starting to define the speaker data schema in the `db.json` structure, aiming for dual language content, and I am aiming for readability to match the look. The speaker schema structure is: id, name, university, major, admissionYear, story, lectureTopic, lectureTime, and photoColor.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will start by editing `metadata.json` to configure the application\'s official name, description, and major capabilities. Since it is a full-stack educational event landing page with custom administrative CMS tools, setting the name prevents it from being a placeholder."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 12
      nanos: 193262924
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
