  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Designing Database Seed Data**\n\nOkay, I\'m working on the initial database seed data and am focusing on creating a comprehensive set of 16 compelling speaker entries. I\'m building out each speaker with detailed information: names, universities, majors, admission years, compelling bios, lecture topics, and scheduling information, ensuring robust and diverse examples.\n\n\n**Defining Data Structure and Keys**\n\nI\'ve refined the data structure for the seed file. The core keys will be `speakers` (16 entries representing high achievers from Kazakh and international backgrounds), `program` (8-10 schedule slots), `partners` (6-8 organizations), `tickets` (3 categories with pricing and custom links), `subscribers` (initially an empty array), and `settings` (global configurations like event date, venue, and contact info). I\'m leaning toward a simple `admin123` password, or one that is easily configurable, for initial setup.\n\n\n**Implementing Speaker Data**\n\nI\'m now implementing the default `db.json` file, and populating it with the 16 speaker entries. I\'ve integrated a mix of Kazakh and international names, academic institutions, and majors. I\'m focusing on providing the basic details and will soon add the bios and lecture topics.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create a persistent JSON-based database at `/data/db.json`. This database will store the configurations, custom schedules, pricing tickets, list of sponsors, sub-database of newsletter emails, and seed information for 17 real-world inspired speakers who were admitted to Ivy League, Stanford, Oxford, Cambridge, and Nazarbayev University. This ensures the app is fully hydrated and ready, while remaining editable in real time."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 4
      nanos: 119211776
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
