    thinking: "**Considering Initial Setup**\n\nI\'ve successfully seeded the database with a good foundation: 17 speakers, 10 program slots, 6 partners, 3 ticket categories, an empty subscribers list, and the base settings. Now, I\'m shifting my focus towards creating the server file, `server.ts`. I\'m taking a moment to review the installed packages, ensuring a smooth build.\n\n\n**Analyzing Server Endpoints**\n\nI\'m now diving into the `server.ts` file, and considering required dependencies beyond `express`, `path`, and `fs/promises`. I\'ve begun to outline `/api` endpoints with an emphasis on simplicity and efficiency. My current focus is refining endpoints like `GET /api/data`, and `GET /api/speakers`, `GET /api/schedule`, `GET /api/partners`, `POST /api/subscribe`, and establishing admin endpoints with a clear authentication flow via `POST /api/admin/login`.\n\n\n**Defining Admin APIs**\n\nI am now structuring the `/api/admin` endpoints for program, partners, tickets, and subscriber management. I will implement `GET`, `POST`, `PUT`, and `DELETE` methods, and will focus on robust file system operations using a helper function in `server.ts` to ensure safety and synchronization. I will implement a session-token-based authorization system for admin access. Furthermore, I\'ll export subscriber data to a downloadable CSV stream via `/api/admin/subscribers/export`.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will write `server.ts` now, which coordinates the custom full-stack server. In development, it integrates Vite\'s middleware directly into Express to support instantaneous hot refreshes. In production, it compiles smoothly via our `esbuild` structure and serves pre-built assets from `/dist`. All data is loaded or edited inside our persistent JSON file `/data/db.json` with robust transaction-style locking. I will provide full CRUD APIs for speakers, schedule, partners, tickets, custom email subscriptions, and csv downloads for the mailing list."
    thinking_duration {
