  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Considering Speaker Card Design**\n\nI\'m now diving into the `/src/components/SpeakerCard.tsx` component. The primary function will be displaying a speaker list. I\'m exploring the grayscale-to-color hover effect, but hit a snag with the custom illustrations/avatars. How do I achieve this color-transition elegantly without using external photos? I need a solution.\n\n\n**Designing Avatar Gradients**\n\nI\'ve decided to pursue typographic badges or modern avatar circles within the speaker cards. The plan is to have an elegant box featuring speaker initials with a gradient background. In default state, this will be grayscale, transitioning to a colorful gradient upon hover, based on the speaker\'s affiliation. I\'m thinking of using SVG gradients for stylish university layouts, which start grayed out and become vivid on hover to satisfy the design requirement.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create `/src/components/SpeakerCard.tsx`, which renders each presenter with interactive grayscale-to-vivid university color hover actions. Clicking a card opens a modern, transitions-equipped modal displaying the speaker\'s detailed academic path, essays strategy, and their scheduled session. This fulfills the user\'s explicit request for interactive hover effects and descriptive dialog popups."
